  "prompt": "What universities does Pall recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Pall Corporation, a global leader in filtration, separation, and purification technologies, typically recruits new graduates from a variety of universities, focusing on institutions known for strong engineering, life sciences, and technical programs. While the specific universities can vary based on geographic location and specific recruitment initiatives, Pall often targets schools with robust engineering, chemistry, materials science, biotechnology, and environmental science programs.\n\nKey majors that Pall is generally interested in include:\n\n1. Chemical Engineering\n2. Mechanical Engineering\n3. Electrical Engineering\n4. Biomedical Engineering\n5. Chemistry\n6. Biochemistry\n7. Biotechnology\n8. Environmental Science/Engineering\n9. Materials Science\n\nFor the most precise information, it would be beneficial to consult Pall\u2019s careers page or reach out directly to their recruitment team, as their hiring priorities may have specific targets based on current organizational goals and project needs.",
